                 geometry of binocular vision. In standard retinal space, the
                 composite decussation line for the uncrossed retinal
                 projection is located 64° away from the retinal pole.
                 Projecting anatomically defined uncrossed retinal projections
                 into visual space gives binocular congruence if the optical
